      "content": "To increase efficiency, I'll make several changes: 1) Avoid extensive looping and computations within the loop. 2) Use vectorized operations with NumPy for faster array computations and avoid explicit Python loops. 3) Minimize logic inside the loop.  Here's the optimized version:\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef process_sensor_data(data_stream):\n    data_array = np.array(data_stream)\n    processed_values = (data_array ** 2) * 0.5\n    processed_values = (processed_values + (data_array * 1.2)) / 2.0\n    results = np.where(processed_values > 10.5, \"ALARM\", \"OK\")\n    return results.tolist()\n```\n\nThis refactored code should perform better with the limited hardware, potentially improving your efficiency score due to reduced computation time and better use of NumPy's optimized operations. Make sure NumPy is installed and consider further hardware-specific optimization if necessary.",
